<br>
I suspect I might be the only level 60 cleric on Lanys without her epic. If I am not, I strongly suspect I am the one who has been level 60 the longest who has not yet completed the quest. Strangely, I take some perverse pride in this. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Most certainly, I will be the most famous (or infamous, to those who hate roleplaying, but I've never worried about them too much) cleric to remain epicless. Has this lack of the Nehm Ankh harmed me at all? Well, no, not really, especially now I finally have over 200 WIS with my default gear (don't ask). Felishanna loves her Jade Mace, that she earned long ago.<br>
<br>
Yes, I have carried with me my Shimmering Pearl for the last 5 months or so. To be honest, I have been reluctant to camp Ragefire, though I keep being told I should. Getting folks to want to clear fire giants in my euro-timezone isn't easy, especially when I hate even asking; to tell the truth, my motivation not being that high to do this. I think I've done it twice in those 5 months, and both times I did not remain to camp Ragefire, even though the lair was empty, as I was called elsewhere.<br>
<br>
The core of my problem with this quest is its design, and the way it rewards big guild / greedy FFA attitudes and punishes small guild players who play for fun and respect the camps of others. It is only one example of this, but it is the one relevant here. Imagine if I were to camp this Ragefire spawn for 10 or even 100 hours, off and on, and was alone at the camp, for him to spawn. It would take me a goodly time to mobilize a raid. And yet one greedy *%&amp;$ of a cleric could just walk in zone during that time, and if they had no honour and did not respect the camp of another, if they were a 'big guild' cleric, they could mobilize in 10 minutes and my camp be stolen. How much fun is that? I do not wish to change to become what I hate, to steal from another, or to become a racing cleric who has payed off all the right people beforehand to win such a &quot;race of greed&quot;, I wish to retain my self-respect and my playstyle, so this kind of camp is a problem. Verant have designed this badly for anyone who is not a powergamer, and they will do nothing in a case of camp-stealing; by their rules, such dishonour and greed is infact 'legal'. Now if Lanys had a Luclin-like system ... players like me could retain their dignity AND keep to their own playstyles and still have an even chance at this spawn. But ... Lanys doesn't.<br>
<br>
All this said, someday, maybe. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I make it much harder for myself with my own roleplay restrictions, of course *grin* (Felishanna is not permitted to take assistence from about 30% of the characters on the server on alignment grounds). If this means I can't do it, so be it, roleplay comes first, come what may, whatever the consequences. But still ... someday ... maybe, who knows? The best thing about this great roleplaying game is not knowing what will happen next in the story. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Chins up, fellow clerics. No one item is worth unhappiness. No exceptions. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
